      "side": 1,
      "message": "This change alters behaviour here. Previously, it only caused the tuner to enter low power mode. Now it also results the tuner driver calling tuner_power(false). That will decrease power consumption while the radio is paused, but it may also cause some settings to be forgotten. In radio_start(), RADIO_REGION and RADIO_FORCE_MONO are only set if radio_status \u003d\u003d FMRADIO_OFF.\n\nThe tuner drivers could be changed to not call tuner_power(false) when the argument is 2, or the pause state could be eliminated in radio.c. I\u0027m not sure if having a separate pause state on the hardware level is beneficial. The additional initialization after FMRADIO_OFF should take virtually no time from a user perspective. The only disadvantage I can think of is that switching tuner power might cause a click or pop sound.",
      "revId": "fdfcb57669b99c0a5696d48f624cf66bdd4e1718",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
      "unresolved": false
    },
